Audience: Sales Engineers, Account Executives, Value Consultants.

Executive Summary

Currently, the "Research Company" feature in ValueOS is transactional: users perform a one-time search to gather data for a Value Case. The Intel Stream initiative transforms this static action into a continuous, active monitoring loop. By converting a "Search" into a "Subscription," ValueOS will push relevant, high-impact signals (executive changes, financial shifts, strategic pivots) directly to the user. This ensures Value Cases remain living documents, increasing user retention and the accuracy of value projections.2. Problem StatementStatic Data: Value Cases are often built on data that becomes stale within weeks.Missed Triggers: Users manually scouring Google News or LinkedIn often miss critical events (e.g., a new CTO with a specific bias) that should fundamentally change their sales strategy or value calculation.Low Engagement: Users typically leave the platform once the case is "done," only returning when forced. We lack a "hook" for daily engagement.3. The Solution: "Intel Stream"We will introduce an automated intelligence layer that monitors companies associated with active or draft cases. When a meaningful signal is detected, it is processed not just as news, but as a Value Trigger—prompting specific updates to the user's economic models.Key Value Proposition"Don't just build a business case; keep it alive. ValueOS watches your prospects so you don't have to."4. User Journey & ExperiencePhase 1: The Setup (The Hook)Current State: User clicks "Research Company" $\rightarrow$ Gets Data $\rightarrow$ Leaves.New State: User clicks "Research Company" $\rightarrow$ ValueOS generates profile $\rightarrow$ Auto-subscribes user to "Major Signals" for this account.UI Update: A toggle appears on the Case Creation screen: "Monitor this account for strategic shifts?" (Default: Checked).Phase 2: The Stream (The Dashboard Widget)A new widget appears on the Home Dashboard (replacing or sitting alongside "Start Something New").Widget Title: "Account Signals" or "Intelligence Feed"Content: A chronological feed of high-impact events for "Committed" and "In Progress" cases.Visuals:🔴 Risk: "Beta Inc announced 10% workforce reduction." (Impact: Efficiency Model)🟢 Opportunity: "Gamma Ltd CEO mentions 'Digital Transformation' in Q3 earning call." (Impact: Strategic Alignment)Phase 3: The Action (Closing the Loop)The differentiator is actionability. We do not just show news; we link it to the Value Case.Scenario: ValueOS detects a drop in stock price for Delta Corp.Notification: "Delta Corp stock is down. Pressure on OPEX may increase."CTA: "Review Assumptions" button.Result: Clicking the button takes the user directly to the "Cost Assumptions" tab of the Delta Corp case.5. Functional RequirementsA. Data Ingestion (The "Ears")We need to tap into API streams for three specific categories of intel:People Intelligence: Key hires/fires (C-Suite, VPs). Source: LinkedIn API, ZoomInfo, etc.Financial Intelligence: 10-K/10-Q filings, stock performance, earnings transcripts. Source: AlphaSense, seekingAlpha, or financial APIs.Technographic Intelligence: Changes to their tech stack (e.g., buying a competitor or complementary tool). Source: BuiltWith, G2 Track.B. Signal Filtering (The "Brain")To avoid noise, the system must filter for relevance.Irrelevant: "Acme Corp sponsors a charity 5k." (Do not show)Relevant: "Acme Corp misses revenue targets by 15%." (Show high priority)C. UI ComponentsDashboard Feed: A card-based list of recent signals.Case Header Badge: Inside a specific case (e.g., "Acme Corp Value Case"), add a "Signals" badge with a counter (e.g., "3 New Updates").Email Digest: A weekly "Account Watch" email summarizing top signals for their active portfolio.6. Success Metrics (KPIs)Engagement: % of users who click on a Signal to view a Case.Case Longevity: Average time a Value Case remains "active" (last edited date). Goal: Increase from 2 weeks to 3 months.Retention: Daily Active Users (DAU) increase due to users checking the "Intel Stream."7. Roadmap / PhasingPhase 1 (MVP): Basic financial news integration. "Research Company" automatically adds the company to a "Watchlist." Simple dashboard widget.Phase 2 (Context): "Smart Nudges." The system identifies which model input is affected (e.g., if "Revenue" is mentioned, link to Revenue Uplift model).Phase 3 (CRM Sync): Push these insights back into Salesforce/HubSpot notes fields automatically.
